&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-5468 An employee at the SCP Foundation accidentally found SCP-5468 (???. Exe) installed on his computer on the internet and opened it, after which he said that ???. Exe did not leave him alone, and he died 3 or 2 days later. After these happened, other employees in the foundation checked if there was ???. exe on another computer in the world ???. exe was deleted from approximately 300 computers in the world and successfully contained.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCP-5468 is a computer virus, but not only that, people who install and open SCP-5468 first will see a cmd file of ??? texts, and then these same texts will appear on the person&#039;s phone and then on all devices on the internet that the person is connected to. After that, an unknown number will send messages from the person&#039;s phone. The messages are usually:&lt;br /&gt;
1- I know your name&lt;br /&gt;
2- I can control you&lt;br /&gt;
3- I am not a hacker&lt;br /&gt;
4- I am ???. Exe&lt;br /&gt;
5- You shouldn&#039;t have done this&lt;br /&gt;
Then the person using the phone is always in mind ??? writings and words will appear after that person will start going crazy The person will can&#039;t sleep because of the ??? words and eventually the person will begin to have hallucinations and die after 1 or 2 days. How ???.exe do these effects and who sent the messages is still unknown&lt;/p&gt;
