					<![CDATA[
						 <div style="text-align: center;"> <p><strong>« <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/news-08-2020">August 2020</a> | <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/news-09-2020">September 2020</a></span> | <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/news-10-2020">October 2020</a> »</strong></p> </div> <div style="border: 2px solid black; background-color: Moccasin;"> <p style="text-align: center;">The dynamic nature of this wiki means that linked pages might get moved, renamed, deleted, or replaced. Old news pages remain as time capsules and are not updated to account for these changes.</p> </div> <p><span style="font-size:75%;">This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-373305-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >1</a></sup>, and fan-content for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</span></p> <h4><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h4> <ul> <li><a href="https://www.gofundme.com/f/scp-legal-funds">A hearing</a> in the SCP trademark case took place this month. Another court session was scheduled for next month.</li> </ul> <ul> <li><a href="http://fondationscp.wikidot.com/">SCP-FR</a> has a new domain - <a href="http://fondationscp.fr/">http://fondationscp.fr/</a> - that redirects visitors to the SCP-FR wiki.</li> </ul> <ul> <li><a href="http://scp-wiki-de.wikidot.com/">SCP-DE</a>'s mentor system that helps newcomers to the site now has <a href="http://scp-wiki-de.wikidot.com/mentoren">an information page</a>.</li> </ul> <ul> <li>SCP-DE also accepted a large side canon - <a href="http://scp-wiki-de.wikidot.com/projekt-trickster">Project Trickster</a> - into the official DE canon.</li> </ul> <ul> <li><a href="http://scp-es.com/">SCP-ES</a> is continuing its frequent micro-contests that take place on the forums. <a href="http://scp-es.com/forum/t-13698749/de-regreso-a-las-andadas:reto-de-escritura">The lastest one</a> was constrained to take place over the course of just five hours.</li> </ul> <ul> <li>The latest of <a href="http://ko.scp-wiki.net/">SCP-KO</a>'s <a href="http://ko.scp-wiki.net/bimonthly-contests-2020#toc4">bimonthly contests</a> concluded this month.</li> </ul> <h4><span>Featured Articles</span></h4> <ul> <li><a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4823">SCP-4823</a> (&quot;The Whole World Has Gone Bananas&quot;) by Serabus<br /> Featured by Ocuin, Flopmind, and REDESERT<br /></li> </ul> <blockquote> <p>Following entry, SCP-4823 will unpeel itself.</p> </blockquote> <ul> <li><a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/remember">&quot;REMEMBER&quot;</a> by Cerastes<br /> Featured by Truc Linh, Comrade Waldo, and Dr Sage Evergreen<br /></li> </ul> <blockquote> <p>Cain didn't have the luxury of forgetting why he did it&#8230;</p> </blockquote> <ul> <li><a href="http://scpwiki.com/a-song-that-is-unfortunately-about-toes">&quot;Single: untitled&quot;</a> by oboebandgeek99<br /> Featured by KaraKatt and Dr Gallium<br /></li> </ul> <blockquote> <p>While this is inspired by true things(ish) I've embellished the story.</p> </blockquote> <h4><span>Reviewer's Spotlight Articles</span></h4> <p><a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5380">SCP-5380</a>: My World by chiifu featured by KaraKatt<br /> <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5595">SCP-5595</a>: Geoffrey Quincy Harrison the Third: Site-Director, Gumball Machine by PlaguePJPfeatured by redesert<br /> <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/i-just-wanna-survive">I Don't Wanna Be Special (I Just Wanna Survive)</a> by OboeBandGeek99<br /> featured by Naveil<br /> <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5335">SCP-5335</a>: The Freudian Split by MalyceGraves<br /> Featured by Francis Scalia</p> <div id="toc" class="floatright"> <div id="toc-action-bar"><a href="javascript:;" >Fold</a><a style="display: none" href="javascript:;" >Unfold</a></div> <div class="title">Table of Contents</div> <div id="toc-list"> <div style="margin-left: 3em;"><a href="#toc0">Week of September 1st:</a></div> <div style="margin-left: 3em;"><a href="#toc1">Week of September 8th:</a></div> <div style="margin-left: 3em;"><a href="#toc2">Week of September 15th:</a></div> <div style="margin-left: 3em;"><a href="#toc3">Week of September 22nd:</a></div> <div style="margin-left: 3em;"><a href="#toc4">Canon Renaissance Contest Entries</a></div> <div style="margin-left: 3em;"><a href="#toc5">Fanart</a></div> </div> </div> <hr /> <p>You will notice little '📈' emojis beside some articles. That denotes SCP articles which were under 30 and tales which were under 20 when this edition of site news was posted. Give them a little love! Speaking from personal experience, the most frustrating thing that can happen to an article is not deletion, but stagnating below 20 without any comments. So try to read, vote, and comment on these articles! They're often hidden gems :)</p> <h3><span>Week of September 1st:</span></h3> <h4><span>SCPs</span></h4> <ul> <li>📈 <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5516">SCP-5516</a> (&quot;101 Lobster Friends&quot;) - Nothing more, nothing less. Account made by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dododevil" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1854139&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204914" alt="DodoDevil" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1854139)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dododevil" >DodoDevil</a></span>.</li> <li>📈 <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-3195">SCP-3195</a> (&quot;The Fault in Our Star&quot;) - I knew that this star was a troublemaker. Of course, it's her fault. Of course. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/marcelles-raynes" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5722579&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204914" alt="Marcelles_Raynes" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5722579)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/marcelles-raynes" >Marcelles_Raynes</a></span>.</li> <li>📈 <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5705">SCP-5705</a> (&quot;Powered by Thorium!™&quot;) - Here's another material who can be a power source for you. COVID-19 can't stop us creating them. Made by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/iszth" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5404858&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204914" alt="Iszth" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5404858)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/iszth" >Iszth</a></span>.</li> <li><a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5147">SCP-5147</a> (&quot;The Mannequin Troupe&quot;) - This is not for your entertainment. Brought to you by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirslash47" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6438262&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204914" alt="Sirslash47" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6438262)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirslash47" >Sirslash47</a></span>.</li> <li><a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5494">SCP-5494</a> (&quot;The Lords of the Beneath World&quot;) - We still wait to know what exact beneath world they rule, they still have to come back to us. Investigations made by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/harryblank" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6479803&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204914" alt="HarryBlank" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6479803)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/harryblank" >HarryBlank</a></span>.</li> <li><a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2754">SCP-2754</a> (&quot;A Festival For One, a Festival For None.&quot;) - It's not the Fyre Festival II. Written by <span