ground-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1613974)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" >UraniumEmpire</a></span> a link to your piece and she'll post it on next month's &quot;Last Month's Pieces and Topic&quot; section!</p> <p>For artists: try to link to whatever social media page is hosting the art. It saves us space and ensures we have a solid reference.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="content-panel centered"> <div class="panel-heading"> <p>Last Month's Pieces and Topic</p> </div> <div class="panel-body"> <h2><span><a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/fault-lines">Fault Lines</a> and the Gulf canon</span></h2> </div> <div class="panel-footer"> <p>The best of the past.</p> </div> </div> <div class="content-panel centered"> <div class="panel-heading"> <p>Topic + pick of this month!</p> </div> <div class="panel-body"> <h2><span><a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/new-age-hub">New Age</a></span></h2> </div> <div class="panel-footer"> <p>This month's piece.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>New Age is a novel-length trilogy about the Chaos Insurgency. It's a bit of a long read, so let's not worry too much about the description, alright?</p> <h3><span>This month's challenge:</span></h3> <ul> <li><strong>For writers:</strong> &#8230; why don't you take a break for this one? It's a long read.</li> <li><strong>For artists:</strong> And if you feel inspired to draw a scene from it afterwards&#8230; well, the more the merrier!</li> </ul> <p>by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1613974&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204914" alt="UraniumEmpire" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1613974)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" >UraniumEmpire</a></span></p> <div class="footnotes-footer"> <div class="title">Footnotes</div> <div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-941856-1"><a href="javascript:;" >1</a>. Meaning a hub dedicated exclusively or primarily to the topic. GoI Formats would <em>not</em> count unless the primary content for the GoI is its formats.</div> </div> 
